settings.pressRelease_pressHead: Over 50pc of Indian men facing hair loss below 25: Study
settings.pressRelease_pressContent: Hyderabad: Traya, India’s first-ever health-tech brand to help treat hair loss internally, unveils noteworthy findings from its expansive study involving over 500,000 men. The data highlights that 50.31% of Indian men experiencing hair loss are under the age of 25. As per the study, 25.89% men below the age of 21 are already at Stage 3 and beyond. As the age bracket shifts to 21-25 years old, this number further increases to 33.35%. With the average Traya customer age being 28, it is an evident indication that hair loss has become a serious concern in this demographic.

settings.pressRelease_pressHead: How Traya is Transforming Hair Health with a Holistic Approach
settings.pressRelease_pressContent: The world of healthcare is constantly evolving, and in recent years, the focus has expanded beyond traditional medicine to holistic wellness. One area that has seen significant transformation is hair health. Hair loss, a common concern for many, has spurred innovative solutions that delve into the root causes of the problem. Traya, a pioneering health-tech brand, has emerged as a game-changer in the industry. Co-founded by Saloni Anand, Traya takes a comprehensive approach to addressing hair loss, combining Ayurveda, Dermatology, and Nutrition. In this article, we explore the inspiring journey of Traya's inception, its unique value in the healthcare industry, its funding journey, and its vision for the future.

settings.pressRelease_pressHead: Traya defines how good gut bacteria is your hair’s new... saviour
settings.pressRelease_pressContent: A healthy you begins with a healthy gut and a balanced microbiome is what we mean when we say "healthy gut." The bacteria that live inside our gut play a crucial role in determining not just our gut health but also the quality of our hair. Now why would these creepy crawlies be beneficial for hair one might wonder…. Well, these microorganisms have a tool box available in the form of enzymes which help them break down food to useful forms of nutrients. Traya's Dietician Nishita Suratkal talks us through gut bacteria and how these nutrients are what is required for ideal hair growth.

settings.visionors-about-head: Changing The Conversation Around Hair Loss: Saloni Anand Talks About Building Her Brand Traya
settings.visionors-about-content: In her quest to find a therapy for her husband’s untimely hair loss, Saloni Anand, co-founder of Traya, a young techie-marketer, uncovered a novel treatment strategy supported by the strength of three sciences: Ayurveda, Nutrition, and Dermatology. Traya is India’s first health-tech company to offer solutions for hair loss that have been approved by doctors and are supported by extensive research.

settings.visionors-about-head: ‘My Husband’s Hairfall Inspired These Hair Solutions’: Engineer’s Biz Finds 2.5 Lakh Customers
settings.visionors-about-content: Saloni Anand started Traya to help people grappling with hair loss by changing shampoos and searching for quick fixes. The venture offers a five-month long programme and currently has over 2.5 lakh customers.

settings.visionors-about-content: Founded by husband-wife duo Saloni and Altaf Saiyed, the start-up was born out of the couple's personal health issues when bith of them realized that Ayurveda and nutrition could help them to create a preventive approach.

settings.visionors-about-head: ‘Women hesitate to talk about their achievements, but as an entrepreneur, you have to sell yourself’
settings.visionors-about-content: How Saloni Anand, a mom of one and the founder of Traya, manages to stop multitasking “Keep work off WhatsApp and WhatsApp off work.” That’s entrepreneur Saloni Anand’s mantra for managing a successful start-up while parenting a young child. Easier said than done when you’ve been added to a fourth WhatsApp group just this week. But Anand’s point is really about leaving the phone in your bag and focussing on one task at a time.

settings.visionors-about-head: Don’t Be Busy Finding Work-Life Balance
settings.visionors-about-content: Being an entrepreneur involves making sacrifices to do well in a competitive business world. It means you have a lot of important tasks and potential problems to deal with. This fast-paced environment can make it hard to stay productive and have a good balance between work and personal life, which can be tough.
